&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;on-site&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Specialty Pharmacy Care Coordinator in &lt;strong&gt;Lufkin, TX &lt;/strong&gt;to help us make specialty medications more accessible and affordable for patients. Keep reading to learn more about the role, our team and why House Rx is the right next step in your career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a pivotal member of the House Rx team, you will work closely with specialty care clinics and the House Rx team to improve the specialty pharmacy experience for patients and their caregivers. &lt;strong&gt;This is an on-site role in Lufkin, TX.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete prior authorizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source financial assistance on behalf of patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process pharmacy claims&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate medication dispensing and shipping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the patient experience by answering questions and requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a liaison between the patient, their provider and the pharmacist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About You&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have mastered all the core pharmacy technician skills, such as processing claims and dispensing medications, and are ready to expand your career&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable engaging with patients, providers, and all members of the care team both in-person and over the phone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience navigating specialty medication benefits investigation, prior authorization, and financial assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are excited about working in a start-up environment and helping to build workflows and processes from the ground up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy learning new technologies and are proficient in some common pharmacy software systems (QS1, ComputerRx, PioneerRx, WAM, etc). Bonus points if you have worked in EMR systems (EPIC, Cerner, NextGen, etc) or specialty pharmacy systems (Therigy, Asembia1, ScriptMed, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are familiar with specialty medications, including medications used in autoimmune, endocrinology, and oncology. Willingness to learn therapeutic areas you are not familiar with is great&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a creative problem solver interested in positively impacting each patient’s pharmacy experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an initiative taking individual contributor who can also promote teamwork and collaboration amongst colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pharmacy technician, licensed practical nurse or similar licensure as may be required in the applicable state&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technician registration or licensure in State of employment, national certification as CPhT is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may have the opportunity to travel to our client sites 10-15% of the time&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excited about the opportunity, but worried you don’t meet all the requirements? Apply anyway, and give us both the chance to find out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expected Hourly Rate:&amp;nbsp; $22/hr - $32/hr&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This range represents the low and high end of the anticipated base salary/wage. The actual base salary/wage will depend on several factors, including experience, knowledge, and skills. Actual compensation packages may include other elements equity, paid time off and benefits.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;br&gt;Why You Should Join Our Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A career at House Rx offers the chance to work with a talented group of entrepreneurs, healthcare professionals, and technology builders who are passionate about improving specialty care and making it easier for patients to access the medication that they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At House Rx, we strive to

&lt;p&gt;At House Rx, we&#39;re driven by something special: making specialty medications more accessible and affordable for patients who need them most. Our product, design, and engineering team, part of our broader 300+ person company, is the backbone of that mission, building the systems, workflows, and data infrastructure that help get life-saving drugs into patients&#39; hands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our engineering function is growing and we&#39;re bringing on a Director of Engineering. This is a high-impact role for a builder and leader who wants their work to matter. We&#39;d love to connect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Engineering, you will own the technical execution and team leadership of several core engineering pods at House Rx. You&#39;ll lead a team of 18, including two Engineering Managers and their respective pods, a Staff Engineer, the QA team, and several direct IC engineers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll report to the VP of Engineering and work alongside a peer Director of Engineering. This is a high-visibility leadership role with real technical expectations. You won&#39;t be a distant executive. You&#39;ll be in the work: reviewing architecture, unblocking teams, making hard calls, and modeling what great looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive the Team Forward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the pace and raise the bar. Establish clear goals, cut through ambiguity, and hold the team accountable to shipping meaningful work with high quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product and design to shape the roadmap, make smart trade-offs, and keep engineering unblocking the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build engineering processes that scale: sprint rhythms, incident response, code review standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks early and drive to resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead &amp;amp; Develop People&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop your team across all levels, providing coaching, career development, and performance feedback. Hold managers accountable for the output of their pods while investing equally in every direct report&#39;s growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a culture of high standards and continuous growth, where engineers do some of the best work of their careers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain a high bar for talent; define what great looks like and hold the standard&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and develop future engineering leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Technical Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide architectural oversight across your pods, ensuring systems are scalable, maintainable, and built to last.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion best practices across code quality, observability, testing, and system design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay close to the technical work to earn trust, spot issues early, and give grounded feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Champion AI-Forward Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead by example with AI development tools and set clear expectations for the team to do the same.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and introduce AI tooling that improves developer velocity, code quality, and product capability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a team culture that treats AI as a genuine productivity multiplier, not a novelty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define House Rx&#39;s approach to responsible, high-leverage AI use in engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years in software engineering, with 3+ years in engineering management, ideally including experience managing managers or leading multiple teams.&lt;/li&gt;
