&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a highly organized and detail-oriented IT Specialist to join our Security &amp;amp; IT team to help us make specialty medications more accessible and affordable for patients. Keep reading to learn more about the role, our team, and why House Rx is the right next step in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a hands-on IT Specialist position based onsite in Pittsburgh, aligned to&lt;strong&gt; Pacific Time working hours (approximately 11:00AM - 8:00PM ET)&lt;/strong&gt;. You will be a critical part of House Rx’s Security &amp;amp; IT team, responsible for keeping our employees productive, supported, and properly equipped from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will serve as the primary point of contact for employee IT needs, handle traditional IT support requests, and play a key role in building, provisioning, and deploying laptops for onboarding. This role is ideal for someone who enjoys being close to the work, values operational excellence, and takes pride in delivering a great internal support experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IT Support &amp;amp; Employee Assistance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a point of contact for employee IT Support requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot hardware and software issues across macOS and Windows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely, clear, and empathetic support to employees across departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate complex issues appropriately while owning communication and resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device Provisioning &amp;amp; Lifecycle Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, configure, and deploy laptops for new hires and replacements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare devices with required OS configuration, security tooling, and applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full device lifecycle including provisioning, shipping, repairs, replacements, and decommissioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate asset tracking and inventory records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identity, Access, &amp;amp; SaaS Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support user access and lifecycle events in tools such as Google Workspace, Okta, Slack, Dialpad, and other SaaS platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with account provisioning, deprovisioning, and access troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in an IT support or IT Specialist role, with hands-on experience supporting users and maintaining tools such as Okta, Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, and Slack. You are eager to learn, take ownership of issues, and improve systems over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;With your robust analytical acumen, you demonstrate an ability to promptly identify and overcome intricate technical obstacles. Your skill in critical thinking underpins this ability, enabling efficient problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, allowing you to collaborate seamlessly with diverse teams and articulate complex ideas in a clear manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You value teamwork and understand the importance of clear communication, especially in a remote-first environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a foundational understanding of IT security principles and compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range: $70,000 - $90,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This range represents the low and high end of the anticipated base salary/wage. The actual base salary/wage will depend on several factors, including experience, knowledge, and skills. Actual compensation packages may include other elements equity, paid ti

&lt;p&gt;House Rx is hiring an &lt;strong&gt;Office&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Support Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;to join our IT &amp;amp; Office Support team to help us make specialty medications more accessible and affordable for patients. Keep reading to learn more about the role, our team, and why House Rx is the right next step in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an onsite, entry-level Office Support Specialist position based in our Pittsburgh Hub. You will be an integral part of the day-to-day experience at the House Rx Hub, supporting the smooth operation of our office environment. You&amp;nbsp;will be the go-to person for keeping our office running efficiently, from managing shipments and supplies to creating a welcoming and well-stocked workplace for our team. This role can support all areas of the office and leadership team so role responsibilities can look different on a day to day basis and can go beyond what is listed in this job description.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Office Support Specialist who thrives on variety and isn&#39;t afraid to roll up their sleeves. No two days look the same here, one morning you might be restocking supplies and coordinating a team lunch, the next you&#39;re helping onboard a new hire or troubleshooting why the printer is jammed again. If you&#39;re someone who gets a quiet satisfaction from making chaos feel effortless, this will be a great fit.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who is proactive, takes pride in the details, and enjoys being the person who makes everything run smoothly behind the scenes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shipping &amp;amp; Mail&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inbound and outbound shipments and daily mail distribution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with carriers and vendors to ensure timely deliveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and log packages and maintain accurate shipping records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with ordering and shipping supplies to our clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Office Supply &amp;amp; Inventory Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and restock office supplies, kitchen items, and shared spaces including coffee and breakroom essentials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place and track supply orders, managing relationships with vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized, well-stocked, and tidy common areas throughout the office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Office Coordination &amp;amp; Events&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the first point of contact for visitors, vendors, and anyone who walks through the door&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute office events, team celebrations, and company parties, with support from the People and Event Teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in coordinating meetings, office logistics, and ad hoc operational needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing vendor relationships and fielding service requests (think: internet, cleaning, building management)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field the random, because there&#39;s always something that needs handling and someone has to be great at it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the office leadership with various office projects and initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are highly organized with strong attention to detail and the ability to juggle multiple tasks at once - Detail-oriented enough to catch things before they become problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take initiative and follow through, if you see something that needs to be done, you do it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are resourceful and self-directed, you figure things out without waiting to be told.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent communication skills and

&lt;p&gt;House Rx is on a mission to make specialty medications more affordable and accessible for patients suffering from chronic illnesses like cancer and autoimmune disorders. We provide clinics with specialized technology and support from pharmacists and care coordinators to dispense medication directly to their patients, known as medically integrated dispensing (MID). &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This work will directly contribute to the company’s mission of making specialty medications affordable and accessible for patients— keep reading to learn more about the role, our team, and why House Rx is the right next step in your career! Applicants must be based in the United States.&amp;nbsp; This role is available to West Coast candidates and/or candidates that are comfortable working West Coast hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking an experienced and dynamic Sr. Customer Success Manager with experience in Oncology to lead our customer initiatives by balancing three key responsibilities: Customer Success, Pharmacy Operational Management, and Financial Growth. This role requires expertise in building relationships, overseeing operations, and driving financial performance to ensure the success of our oncology customer programs. This role will require travel to customer sites up to 50% of the time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Success:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship Building:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish and maintain strong, collaborative relationships with key stakeholders, including dispensers, clinic staff, financial personnel, providers, and executives. Your ability to connect with stakeholders at all levels is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Effective Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Tailor communication to suit various audiences, ensuring clarity and alignment. From engaging with prior authorization staff on operational details to delivering strategic insights during Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs), your communication should be both clear and impactful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objection Handling:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively address concerns and objections raised by stakeholders. Utilize reassuring and confident communication techniques to advocate for our program and ensure satisfaction across all organizational levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Presentation Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Master the use of House Rx template decks, customizing them to meet specific customer needs. Ensure a polished presentation, adhering to professional standards both onsite and virtually.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Advocacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as the voice of the customer in all internal discussions, effectively communicating their needs and expectations. Your insights should drive internal strategies and decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive Monitoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Regularly monitor communication channels, task queues, and documentation to identify potential operational gaps before they impact customers. Aim for zero emergent escalations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issue Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt; Distinguish between program-related and operational issues, addressing customer expectations independently when possible, and escalating Clin Ops-related concerns as needed. Take ownership of investigations and ensure swift resolutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct bi-weekly operational reviews with internal teams, maintaining a high alignment score based on cross-functional feedback regarding clarity and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
